  "text": "For pollen isolation, rice anther samples were first classified into uninucleate, bicellular, immature tricellular stages by the distance between auricles of the last two leaves and the length of the panicle and the floret [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Then, uninucleate mcirospores (UNMs), bicellular pollen (BCP), and immature tricellular pollen (TCP) were isolated from the classified anthers at the corresponding stages.",
